## Code Style

### General Principles
- 2-space indentation for HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JSON, YAML
- 4-space indentation for PHP
- 120 character max line length
- Single quotes for strings (unless interpolation needed)
- Strict equality (===) in JavaScript
- Prefer const over let; no var

### HTML
- Semantic HTML5 elements
- Alt attributes on all images
- Lowercase element names and attributes

### CSS
- Modern CSS: custom properties, grid, flexbox
- Mobile-first responsive design
- BEM naming for custom classes

### JavaScript
- ES6+ syntax: arrow functions, destructuring, async/await
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- Avoid mutating function arguments

### PHP
- PSR-12 standards
- Type hints for parameters and returns
- Null coalescing and nullsafe operators
- Early returns

## Security Best Practices

- Sanitize user input before output
- Parameterized queries only
- Never commit secrets or credentials
- Context-appropriate escaping

## Git Conventions

- Conventional commits format
- feat/fix/refactor/docs/style/test/chore
- Imperative mood in messages

## Testing

- Pure functions, dependency injection
- Test behavior over implementation
- Cover edge cases
